🚀 Connect Cursor + Replit with SSH


 Here's a feature you might not know about: you can connect to a Repl from any 
code editor that uses SSH.

That means you can use tools like Cursor's Composer directly with Replit!



 If you just can't let go of those VS Code extensions or Cursor features, give 
our SSH flow a shot!

Watch the video below for a tutorial on connecting via Mac or head over to the 
docs <https://docs.replit.com/replit-workspace/ssh> for a more detailed 
walkthrough.


 <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e2BE8v4Bj-U>

🤓 New in Replit: Deployment Rollbacks


Deployment rollbacks are a new feature that allow you to quickly and 
confidently version your deployments.

Rollbacks allow you to restore a previous successful deployment in one click: 
fix a broken build or a typo in seconds.



Check out our blog post for all the nitty gritty details on Deployment 
Rollbacks, included in Replit Core, as always.

Read more <https://blog.replit.com/introducing-deployment-rollbacks> 

 

